env_keeper_usage:
Registered variable names:
{key_list}

To register: {lb}"action": "set", "key": "CG_<NAME>", "value": "<value>"{rb}
Registered variables can be used as ${lb}CG_<NAME>{rb} in web_request.

note_quill_usage:
How to use note_quill
Write: {lb}"title": "<title>", "body": "<body>"{rb}
Keep the body within 5 lines. Today's file is created automatically if missing.

letter_post_room_notice:
Currently {count} / {max}.
To register: {lb}"emoji": "🎉", "title": "<title>", "body": "<body>"{rb}
To delete only: {lb}"delete": <num>{rb}

orange_md_err_bad_path:
Invalid file path: '{file}'
Only files inside the workspace are allowed.
Example: {lb}"command": "outline", "file": "SOUL.md"{rb}

orange_md_err_not_found:
File not found: '{file}'
Please check the file name.
Example: {lb}"command": "outline", "file": "SOUL.md"{rb}

orange_md_err_no_start:
'start' is required. Specify the start line number as a string.
Example: {lb}"command": "{command}", "file": "SOUL.md", "start": "1", "end": "50"{rb}
To read to the end: {lb}"command": "{command}", "file": "SOUL.md", "start": "10", "end": "*"{rb}

orange_md_err_start_too_big:
'start' ({start}) exceeds the file's line count ({total}).
This file has {total} lines.
Example: {lb}"command": "{command}", "file": "SOUL.md", "start": "1", "end": "{total}"{rb}

orange_md_err_end_before_start:
'end' ({end}) is smaller than 'start' ({start}).
'end' must be at least 'start'.
Example: {lb}"command": "{command}", "file": "SOUL.md", "start": "{start}", "end": "{total}"{rb}

orange_md_err_json_parse:
Failed to parse JSON.
Input must be in JSON format.
Example: {lb}"command": "outline", "file": "SOUL.md"{rb}

orange_md_err_unknown_command:
Unknown command: '{command}'
Valid commands: {valid}
For usage: {lb}"command": "help"{rb}

citron_unknown_command:
Unknown command: '{command}'.
Valid commands: {valid}
If you're not sure how to use this tool: {lb}"command": "help"{rb}

citron_truncate_notice:
--- Display truncated here (the full content is large; only the first ~{limit} tokens are shown).
  Find a specific spot: {lb}"command": "search", "query": "search term"{rb}
  View a range: {lb}"command": "view", "start": "start_line", "end": "end_line"{rb} ---

citron_open_session_exists:
A session already exists ({ef}). Please commit or discard it first.
Example: {lb}"command": "commit"{rb}
Example: {lb}"command": "discard"{rb}

citron_open_not_found:
File not found: {file_arg}
To open an existing file, specify a path inside the workspace.
To create a new file, set create: true.
Example: {lb}"command": "open", "file": "{file_arg}", "create": true, "content": "initial content (optional)"{rb}

citron_open_read_error:
Cannot read the file: {file_arg}
Directories, special files, or files without read permission cannot be edited.
Details: {e}

citron_search_query_required:
The 'query' argument is required. Please specify the search string (substring match, case-sensitive).
Example: {lb}"command": "search", "query": "search term"{rb}
To also see surrounding lines: {lb}"command": "search", "query": "search term", "context": 2{rb}

citron_rewrite_no_newline:
rewrite's 'content' cannot contain newlines (it replaces one line with one line).
To add multiple lines, use insert.
Example: {lb}"command": "insert", "after": "12", "content": "added line 1\nadded line 2"{rb}

citron_delete_start_required:
The 'start' argument is required. Specify the line number to delete.
Example (single line): {lb}"command": "delete", "start": "10"{rb}
Example (range): {lb}"command": "delete", "start": "10", "end": "15"{rb}

citron_range_not_found:
No lines found in range: {start}-{end}
Use view to check current line numbers.
Example: {lb}"command": "view"{rb}

citron_insert_after_required:
The 'after' argument is required. Specify the line number to insert after.
Example: {lb}"command": "insert", "after": "25", "content": "content to insert"{rb}
To insert at the top of file: {lb}"command": "insert", "after": "0", "content": "content"{rb}

citron_insert_after_missing:
Line {after} does not exist. Use view to check current line numbers.
Example: {lb}"command": "view", "start": "1", "end": "50"{rb}
To insert at the top of file: {lb}"command": "insert", "after": "0", "content": "content"{rb}

citron_commit_tmp_prep_failed:
Could not prepare a temp file for writing: {file_path}
Check that the parent directory exists, isn't a directory with the same name, and that you have write permission.
Details: {e}

citron_commit_write_failed:
Could not write the file: {file_path}
Check that the file isn't open in another app and that you have write permission and free space, then commit again.
Details: {e}

citron_corrupted_json:
Session file is corrupted and unreadable. Discard it and reopen.
Example: {lb}"command": "discard"{rb}
Details: {e}
